@NODE N1 "Program application"
@{B}Program application@{UB}

@{B}Sudominator@{UB} is a fast and versatile sudoku puzzle solver. It can be used for
fully automated solving or as an aid for manual solving. Sudominator uses
an optimized brute force algorithm, so it can solve any sudoku assuming it is
resolvable at all. Sudominator can also verify any sudoku for its correctness.

The program has four modes of operation. The @{B}Quick Solve@{UB} mode solves the puzzle
instantly (even on Efika it is a fraction of second). The @{B}Live Solve@{UB} mode shows
the solving process by displaying every solving step at a rate of 40 to 50 steps
per second. Live solving can take several minutes to complete, it can be stopped
at any time however. The @{B}Random Hint@{UB} mode reveals one, randomly selected field.
Finally the @{B}Selected Hint@{UB} mode reveals a field selected with the mouse.

Sudominator can save a sudoku to file and load it later. This feature is useful
for creating a collection of sudoku puzzles. A few example puzzles are included
to the archive as a start. It also allows to use Sudominator as a helper for
manual solution by storing backtrace points.

It should be noted that trying to solve an unsolvable sudoku may take several
minutes, even in Quick mode. It is because Sudominator does its best to find the
solution, even if it does not exist. Then the program tries every possible
position which takes time. Unfortunately Quick Solve mode cannot be stopped.
The only way to stop it in this case, is to kill the program with iKill tool.
It is relatively safe and should not degrade the system stability.
@ENDNODE
@NODE N2 "What is sudoku?"
@{B}What is sudoku?@{UB}

Sudoku is a mathematic puzzle. It consists of 9 × 9 square divided into nine
3 × 3 boxes. The goal of the puzzle is to place a number between 1 and 9 to
every small square. There are three rules to do it:

1. Every number may be used once only in a column.
2. Every number may be used once only in a row.
3. Every number may be used once only in a box.
@ENDNODE
@NODE N3 "Program usage"
@{B}Program usage@{UB}

Program usage is very simple. Most of gadgets in the main window have bubble
help (just point a gadget with the mouse and wait a second or two for a help
bubble). Sudoku fields are choosen with mouse or cursor keys. Digits are entered
with keyboard, a field can be blanked with "0" key or space.

Menu items

Menu @{B}Project@{UB}:
    @{B}New@{UB} (rcommand + n) - clears the whole sudoku.
    @{B}Open...@{UB} (rcommand + o) - opens a sudoku from a file.
    @{B}Save...@{UB} (rcommand + s) - saves a sudoku to a file.
    @{B}About...@{UB} (rcommand + ?) - displays information about Sudominator
      and license text.
    @{B}Quit@{UB} (rcommand + q) - quits the program.

Menu @{B}Edit@{UB}:
	@{B}Copy@{UB} (rcommand + c) - copies sudoku to the system clipboard as text.

Menu @{B}Settings@{UB}:
    @{B}Sudominator...@{UB} - opens Sudominator @{"settings" LINK N6} window.
    @{B}MUI...@{UB} - opens standard MUI preferences window.

@ENDNODE
