@NODE N8 "Sudoku file format"
@{B}Sudoku file format@{UB}

Sudominator stores sudoku in a 41-byte file. Every sudoku field is stored as
a nibble (4 bits) containing either 0 (an empty field) or number from 1 to 9.
Numbers above 9 are invalid.

81 fields of sudoku make 40 and a half of byte. The last byte is completed with
a nibble 0. The order of writing field is line by line from top to bottom. Lines
are saved from left to right, without padding. For example, following sudoku:

+-----+-----+-----+
|9   3|     |2   7|
|     |	 8  |     |
|  8  |  3  |  9  |
+-----+-----+-----+
|    2|1   6|3    |
|1    |     |    2|
|    4|3   5|8    |
+-----+-----+-----+
|  7  |  1  |  6  |
|     |  4  |     |
|2   1|     |5   9|
+-----+-----+-----+

produces byte stream (in hexadecimal):

90 30 00 20 70 00 08 00 00 08 00 30 09 00 02 10
63 00 10 00 00 00 20 04 30 58 00 07 00 10 06 00
00 04 00 00 20 10 00 50 90

@ENDNODE

